      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YOTTIE (6) is a progressive gelding who resumes off some strong efforts against the top three-year-olds last campaign, highlighted by placings in the NSW Derby and Gold Chalice. Hasn't raced since March but should be ready to go off two trial wins at this venue. FIRE AND PASSION (1) put the writing on the wall when working for back-to-back seconds before leading from this barrier for an easy win in the Breeders Classic 3CG Final at this circuit and distance last start. Was behind YOTTIE when they last clashed in the NSW Derby but had earlier beaten that rival in the heats and he is well served by the ace draw. ALWAYSBJOY NZ (2) returns from a NSW Oaks bid where she placed from a wide draw in the heats before finishing down the track in the final. Won four in a row at this circuit and distance prior. Kept up to the mark with a trial win and draws well. IDEAL BRONSKI (5) was runner-up to FIRE AND PASSION from a tough draw in the Breeders Classic. Recorded a string of wins prior so respect.",
